<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Chico City Council — May 5, 2026</title>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap');

  :root {
    --bg: #f5f2ec;
    --surface: #ffffff;
    --surface2: #f0ede6;
    --border: rgba(0,0,0,0.09);
    --border2: rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    --text: #1a1814;
    --text2: #6b6660;
    --text3: #9c9691;
    --accent: #2d5a3d;
    --accent-light: #e8f0eb;
    --red: #8b2020;
    --red-light: #f5e8e8;
    --amber: #7a4f00;
    --amber-light: #fdf3e0;
    --blue: #1a3d6b;
    --blue-light: #e8eef7;
    --tag-h: 22px;
  }

  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* ── Header ── */
  .site-header {
    background: var(--text);
    color: var(--bg);
    padding: 3rem 2rem 2.5rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .site-header::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent), #5a9e70, var(--accent));
  }
  .header-inner { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .header-eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: .12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(245,242,236,.5);
    margin-bottom: .75rem;
  }
  .header-title {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--bg);
    margin-bottom: .5rem;
  }
  .header-title em { font-style: italic; color: rgba(245,242,236,.65); }
  .header-meta {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: rgba(245,242,236,.5);
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: .25rem 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .header-meta span { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: .35rem; }

  /* ── Layout ── */
  .container { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 2rem 4rem; }

  /* ── Stats row ── */
  .stats-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .stat {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
  }
  .stat-label { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: .04em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: .3rem; }
  .stat-val { font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1; }
  .stat-sub { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text2); margin-top: .3rem; }

  /* ── Tabs ── */
  .tabs-wrap { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .tabs {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }
  .tab-btn {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 400;
    padding: 7px 16px;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    color: var(--text2);
    cursor: pointer;
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
    margin-bottom: -0.5px;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .tab-btn:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .tab-btn.active { color: var(--text); border-bottom-color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }
  .panel { display: none; }
  .panel.active { display: block; }

  /* ── Cards ── */
  .card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: .875rem;
    transition: border-color .15s;
  }
  .card:hover { border-color: var(--border2); }
  .card-header { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: .5rem; }
  .card-num { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text3); min-width: 32px; padding-top: 3px; font-weight: 500; }
  .card-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.35; flex: 1; }
  .card-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: .5rem; }
  .card-rec {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text2);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border2);
    padding-left: 10px;
    margin-top: .65rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Badges ── */
  .badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 5px; margin-bottom: .6rem; }
  .badge {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 2px 9px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    height: var(--tag-h);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    letter-spacing: .01em;
  }
  .badge-green { background: var(--accent-light); color: var(--accent); }
  .badge-red   { background: var(--red-light);   color: var(--red); }
  .badge-amber { background: var(--amber-light);  color: var(--amber); }
  .badge-blue  { background: var(--blue-light);   color: var(--blue); }
  .badge-gray  { background: var(--surface2);     color: var(--text2); }

  /* ── Expand ── */
  .expand-btn {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: .5rem;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    transition: opacity .15s;
  }
  .expand-btn:hover { opacity: .75; }
  .expand-btn .chevron { display: inline-block; transition: transform .2s; }
  .expand-btn.open .chevron { transform: rotate(180deg); }
  .detail {
    display: none;
    margin-top: .875rem;
    padding-top: .875rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }
  .detail.open { display: block; }
  .detail-section { margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .detail-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .08em;
    color: var(--text3);
    margin-bottom: .35rem;
  }
  .detail-body { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.65; }
  .pills { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 5px; margin-top: .4rem; }
  .pill {
    font-size: 11px;
    padding: 2px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    border: 0.5px solid;
    background: transparent;
  }
  .pill-for   { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
  .pill-against { border-color: var(--red);  color: var(--red); }
  .pill-neutral { border-color: var(--border2); color: var(--text2); }

  /* ── Lead paragraph ── */
  .lead {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text2);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }
  .lead strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }

  /* ── Timeline ── */
  .timeline { position: relative; padding-left: 24px; margin-top: .5rem; }
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 5px; top: 6px; bottom: 6px;
    width: 1px;
    background: var(--border2);
  }
  .tl-item { position: relative; margin-bottom: 1.1rem; }
  .tl-dot {
    position: absolute;
    left: -21px; top: 5px;
    width: 9px; height: 9px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border2);
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .tl-dot.past    { background: var(--text2); border-color: var(--text2); }
  .tl-dot.current { background: var(--amber); border-color: var(--amber); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--amber-light); }
  .tl-dot.future  { background: var(--surface); border-color: var(--border2); }
  .tl-date { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text3); margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .tl-event { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.4; }
  .tl-sub { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text2); margin-top: 3px; line-height: 1.5; }

  /* ── Ask buttons ── */
  .ask-row { margin-top: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .ask-btn {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 6px 13px;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--text2);
    transition: background .15s, color .15s, border-color .15s;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .ask-btn:hover { background: var(--surface2); color: var(--text); border-color: var(--border2); }
  .ask-btn::after { content: ' ↗'; }

  /* ── Section label ── */
  .section-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: .1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text3);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-top: .25rem;
  }

  /* ── Footer ── */
  .site-footer {
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text3);
  }
  .site-footer a { color: var(--text2); }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .site-header { padding: 2rem 1.25rem 2rem; }
    .container { padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem 3rem; }
    .stats-row { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="site-header">
  <div class="header-inner">
    <div class="header-eyebrow">City of Chico · Regular Meeting</div>
    <h1 class="header-title">Council Briefing<br><em>May 5, 2026</em></h1>
    <div class="header-meta">
      <span>📍 Council Chamber, 421 Main Street</span>
      <span>🕓 Closed Session 4:30 p.m. · Regular Meeting 6:00 p.m.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="container">

  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-label">Agenda items</div>
      <div class="stat-val">17</div>
      <div class="stat-sub">Consent + Hearings + Regular</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-label">Contested items</div>
      <div class="stat-val">3</div>
      <div class="stat-sub">Sewer rates, nuisances, micro&shy;mobility</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-label">Next deadline</div>
      <div class="stat-val">Jun 2</div>
      <div class="stat-sub">Weed abatement &amp; Eaton Rd hearing</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <div class="stat-label">Next meeting</div>
      <div class="stat-val">May 19</div>
      <div class="stat-sub">Budget workshop + FY 26-27 session</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tabs-wrap">
    <div class="tabs" role="tablist">
      <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="showTab('overview', this)">Overview</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('sewer', this)">Sewer rate fight</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('consent', this)">Consent agenda</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('hearings', this)">Public hearings</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('regular', this)">Regular agenda</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" onclick="showTab('closed', this)">Closed session</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ════ OVERVIEW ════ -->
  <div id="overview" class="panel active">
    <div class="lead">
      Today's meeting is dominated by two interconnected fights: a years-long battle over <strong>sewer rate increases</strong> (items 5.1, 5.2, and 5.8), and a continuing effort to define what the city can legally do about <strong>public nuisances</strong> without violating the Warren Settlement (item 5.4). A new shared e-scooter/bike program, downtown parking pilot, and a big fee schedule update round out the action items.
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Top issues</div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <span class="card-num">5.1–5.2</span>
        <span class="card-title">🔴 Sewer rate war — continued from two prior meetings</span>
      </div>
      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge badge-red">Highly contested</span>
        <span class="badge badge-amber">Continued 3× </span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-desc">On March 17, council voted 4-3 to adopt "Option 1" for five-year sewer rate adjustments. Vice Mayor Bennett — on the winning side — then invoked a rare reconsideration procedure. That reconsideration was itself approved 5-2. Now council must revisit both the procedural framework for future rate hearings (5.1) and the underlying rate question (5.2).</div>
      <button class="expand-btn" onclick="toggle('ov1', this)">Full breakdown <span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="detail" id="ov1">
        <div class="detail-section">
          <div class="detail-label">March 17 vote</div>
          <div class="detail-body">4-3 for Option 1. O'Brien, van Overbeek, and Reynolds in opposition. Reconsideration motion later passed 5-2 (Goldstein and Hawley opposed).</div>
          <div class="pills" style="margin-top:.5rem;">
            <span class="pill pill-for">For reconsideration: 5</span>
            <span class="pill pill-against">Against: Goldstein, Hawley</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-section">
          <div class="detail-label">What is Option 1?</div>
          <div class="detail-body">The staff-recommended five-year sewer rate adjustment schedule — intended to address infrastructure funding gaps and long-deferred maintenance in the sewer enterprise fund.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-section">
          <div class="detail-label">Proposition 218 issue (item 5.1)</div>
          <div class="detail-body">Any property-related rate increase requires compliance with Prop 218 (the California "Right to Vote on Taxes" act). The city must adopt formal procedures for a public hearing and majority protest process before any rate hike can take effect. Item 5.1 is a legal prerequisite to item 5.2.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-section">
          <div class="detail-label">Low-income sewer program (item 5.8)</div>
          <div class="detail-body">Councilmember Hawley added a discussion of an affordability program for low-income ratepayers — likely tied to Hawley's opposition to the reconsideration and desire to condition any rate increase on affordability protections.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <span class="card-num">5.4</span>
        <span class="card-title">🟡 Public nuisances vs. the Warren Settlement</span>
      </div>
      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge badge-amber">Politically charged</span>
        <span class="badge badge-gray">Continued from 3/17</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-desc">Mayor Reynolds requested a discussion of what tools the city has to address public nuisances without invalidating the Warren Settlement — a prior legal agreement that constrains how the city can treat unhoused individuals and encampments. This is a recurring tension in Chico politics.</div>
      <button class="expand-btn" onclick="toggle('ov2', this)">Show context <span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="detail" id="ov2">
        <div class="detail-section">
          <div class="detail-label">Background</div>
          <div class="detail-body">The Warren v. Chico lawsuit resulted in a settlement limiting the city's ability to conduct certain sweeps of homeless encampments. The U.S. Supreme Court's 2024 Grants Pass v. Johnson decision shifted the legal landscape, giving cities more latitude to enforce anti-camping ordinances. Mayor Reynolds is exploring options within — or potentially revisiting — the settlement framework.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-section">
          <div class="detail-label">The core tension</div>
          <div class="pills">
            <span class="pill pill-against">Pro-enforcement majority</span>
            <span class="pill pill-for">Housing-first / civil liberties advocates</span>
          </div>
          <div class="detail-body" style="margin-top:.5rem;">The council majority has generally favored stricter enforcement. Advocates argue the city must provide adequate shelter before enforcing anti-camping rules.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <span class="card-num">5.5</span>
        <span class="card-title">🟢 Shared micromobility program (e-scooters / bikes)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge badge-green">Direction item</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-desc">In October 2025, council directed staff to develop a plan for shared micromobility. Staff returns today with an implementation overview covering permitting, right-of-way impacts, and next steps. No vote yet — council direction is the output.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <span class="card-num">5.6</span>
        <span class="card-title">🟢 Downtown "Park &amp; Go" free parking pilot</span>
      </div>
      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge badge-green">Direction item</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-desc">The Downtown PBID wants the city to run a 3-month summer pilot of free 2-hour downtown parking with no kiosk registration required. Staff analyzed operational and financial implications. Council will decide whether to proceed.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ════ SEWER ════ -->
  <div id="sewer" class="panel">
    <div class="lead">The sewer rate saga is the longest-running fight on today's agenda, spanning multiple meetings and reflecting a deep split on the council. Here is the full arc.</div>

    <div class="section-label">Timeline</div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-dot past"></div>
          <div class="tl-date">March 17, 2026</div>
          <div class="tl-event">Council adopts "Option 1" sewer rate plan — 4 to 3</div>
          <div class="tl-sub">O'Brien, van Overbeek, and Reynolds in opposition.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-dot past"></div>
          <div class="tl-date">April 7, 2026</div>
          <div class="tl-event">Vice Mayor Bennett invokes reconsideration under AP&amp;P 10-10</div>
          <div class="tl-sub">Bennett was on the prevailing side — a required condition. Council votes 5-2 (Goldstein, Hawley opposed) to agendize reconsideration.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-dot past"></div>
          <div class="tl-date">April 21, 2026</div>
          <div class="tl-event">Items 5.1 and 5.2 continued — no action taken</div>
          <div class="tl-sub">Pushed to today's meeting.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-dot current"></div>
          <div class="tl-date">May 5, 2026 — TODAY</div>
          <div class="tl-event">Three sewer items on agenda</div>
          <div class="tl-sub">5.1: Prop 218 procedures · 5.2: Reconsideration of Option 1 · 5.8: Low-income sewer program (Hawley request).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-dot future"></div>
          <div class="tl-date">TBD — after today</div>
          <div class="tl-event">If Prop 218 procedures adopted: public notice period begins</div>
          <div class="tl-sub">Ratepayers receive mailed notice. Majority protest period opens. Public hearing required before any rate change takes effect.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tl-item">
          <div class="tl-dot future"></div>
          <div class="tl-date">Future meeting</div>
          <div class="tl-event">Final rate adoption vote (if no majority protest)</div>
          <div class="tl-sub">New rates would then be phased in over five years.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Arguments on each side</div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-title">Arguments for the rate increase (Option 1)</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">The sewer enterprise fund faces long-deferred infrastructure needs. Without rate adjustments, the city risks service degradation and potential state regulatory violations. The five-year phased schedule spreads the cost burden and gives ratepayers time to adjust. Staff recommended this option as financially necessary.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-title">Arguments for reconsideration / against Option 1</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">O'Brien, van Overbeek, and Reynolds opposed the original vote. Vice Mayor Bennett's reconsideration suggests at least one prior yes vote may have changed position. Concerns include: rates rising too fast, insufficient affordability protections for low-income residents (hence item 5.8), and whether the rate study's assumptions are sound. The Finance Committee also flagged concerns about the Highway Construction Cost Index inflator (35.7%).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-title">Proposition 218 — why it matters</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">California's Prop 218 (1996) requires local governments to give written notice to all property owners before raising property-related fees, hold a public hearing, and allow a majority protest that can kill the increase. Item 5.1 — adopting formal hearing procedures — is legally required before any sewer rate can be raised. Without it, any rate increase is legally vulnerable.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ════ CONSENT ════ -->
  <div id="consent" class="panel">
    <div class="lead">Consent agenda items are considered routine and voted on together unless pulled for individual discussion by a councilmember or member of the public.</div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-num">2.1</span><span class="card-title">Sewer connection fee — 1569 E. 8th Street</span></div>
      <div class="badges"><span class="badge badge-green">Routine</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Allows one property to pay its sewer connection fee as an annual assessment on the tax roll rather than all at once. A standard administrative accommodation.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-num">2.2</span><span class="card-title">Eaton Road right-of-way vacation — Sycamore Plaza 3</span></div>
      <div class="badges"><span class="badge badge-green">Routine</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Commercial developer Sycamore Plaza 3, LP is asking the city to abandon a strip of unused public right-of-way on Eaton Road to accommodate new development. Utility companies have no objections. Today's action only schedules a public hearing for June 2 — no final vacation yet.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-num">2.3</span><span class="card-title">Husa Ranch / Nob Hill Park Landscaping &amp; Lighting District — FY 26-27</span></div>
      <div class="badges"><span class="badge badge-green">Routine · Annual</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Annual renewal of the landscaping and lighting district for this neighborhood. Two resolutions: one initiates proceedings, one sets the public hearing for June 2.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-num">2.4</span><span class="card-title">Supplemental appropriation / budget modification No. 2026-ASD-004</span></div>
      <div class="badges"><span class="badge badge-green">Routine</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">A mid-year budget adjustment requested by the Administrative Services Director. These are typically reallocations of existing funds or acceptance of grant money.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-num">2.5</span><span class="card-title">Sale of 1550 Marauder Street to California Water Service</span></div>
      <div class="badges"><span class="badge badge-amber">Requires 5 votes</span></div>
